@EPA awards North Carolina $409.4 million to rebuild &amp; improve drinking water infrastructure.

This is a step in the right direction to aid reconstruction efforts and mitigate future natural disasters. https://t.co/zyIid13XuA

We can’t afford to let CCP-linked companies, like DeepSeek's AI, acquire sensitive U.S. data &amp; embed themselves in the technologies of the future.

@POTUS’s AI Action plan protects national security &amp; promotes advanced, secure U.S. AI globally.
https://t.co/fCXa4EE0xD

🔔 ICYMI 🔔

@POLITICOPro detailed how @SenPeterWelch &amp; I are working to curb harmful robocalls &amp; better protect Americans from being preyed on by criminal enterprises across the globe.

Thanks @AARP &amp; @USTelecom for their support in fighting back against foreign robocalls. https://t.co/cRkO3vPMLi

Great piece from @WSJopinion explaining how 2.8 million Americans are enrolled on multiple government-backed health plans.

@DrOzCMS says this “double dipping” costs taxpayers as much as $14B annually.

Cutting waste in our healthcare system makes all programs more sustainable.

Great news for North Carolina & all who travel through @RDUAirport!

@USDOT has awarded nearly $25M to widen John Brantley Blvd to double the number of lanes to make pick up & drop off easier for passengers at the terminal.

I’m grateful to @SecDuffy as this was a top priority for the NC delegation & look forward to this project’s completion.

For 52 years, we’ve had a speed limit in the sky. It’s time to cut red tape and flight time coast-to-coast.

@boomaero proved supersonic flight is possible without a sonic boom reaching the ground.
 
My SAM Act would legalize civil supersonic flight over land. https://t.co/ITPcwLaIm2

North Carolina is leading the country in driving business. 

@Toyota has been a great partner to our state: delivering on their investments and creating thousands of jobs for hard-working North Carolinians. 

And we’re just getting started. https://t.co/gCZWehclPl

North Carolina is leading the charge in growing a modern, advanced tech industry.

@SchneiderElec’s $700M investment includes a cutting-edge Robotics & Motion Center of Excellence in Raleigh, and modernizing switchgear and power distribution manufacturing in Welcome—creating over 1,000 good-paying jobs for hardworking North Carolinians.
https://t.co/SmHSdz2BrE

What happened to Laken Riley should never happen to any American citizen.

I can’t think of any good reason why a Senator would oppose the Laken Riley Act.

